rComments: Dr. Brown is an excellent professor. She knows EXACTLY what she is talking about and expects a lot from her students. You HAVE to memorize everything to do well in her courses. The assignments are extremely easy IF you follow the rubric she gives. Testing is tough if you don't memorize details. However, it is possible to do well - WORK ETHIC.
Amazing lectures, clear content and articulation of material. Would definitely take a class with this prof again! :)

Had her for HLTB16 and ANTC67. Assignment instructions and rubrics are clear. She does leave some slides blank so you do need to attend lectures. Exams are pretty specific but most of the short answers are like definitions/models, etc. She isn't funny or anything but I really enjoyed her courses. Study hard? EASY A!! Study only a bit? EASY B!! :)

rComments: She is very explicit in describing what she wants for assignments, the rubric tells you exactly how to do well. There is a decent amount of content but if you study there is no way you can fail her exams. She uses multiple types of questions so everyone has an opportunity to do well, m/c, short answer, long answer. She is tough but very fair.

You have two major assignments.  You must attend class because she leaves some of the slides blank.  The midterm was tricky, her questions are very specific and details matter.   Midterm includes: Multiple choice, true false, short answer, AND equations.
